<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/uepiphanyeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Epiphany EQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(10/22/01 3:21:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anyone know anything about the fleeting quiver quest?</span><hr size=1> Here's the recipe:<br>
<br>
high quality lion skin, <br>
griffon feather,<br>
aviak egg oil,<br>
vial of distilled mana, <br>
and<br>
fleeting quiver pattern<br>
<br>
Here's the breakdown:<br>
1) Camp Highland Lions in North Karana.  These are the only mobs that drop HQ Lion Skins, and NK is the only zone they live in.  This is the bottleneck, and it sucks bad.<br>
<br>
2) While going out of your mind in NK, kill a few griffawns, griffenes, and griffons.  Any flavor can drop the Griffon Feathers.  They are much more common than the lion skin, and you'll probably have tons before you ever see a lion skin.<br>
<br>
3) Hit Butcherblock and forage up some Aviak Eggs.<br>
<br>
4) Find a brewer to combine 1 aviak egg and 1 flask of water in a brew barrel to make Aviak Egg Oil.<br>
<br>
5) Buy or make a poison vial.<br>
<br>
6) Buy 2 sapphires.<br>
<br>
7) Find an enchanter to cast Distill Mana.  He will need the poison vial and the 2 sapphires.  This makes the Vial of Distilled Mana.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Buy the Fleeting Quiver Pattern.  I got mine in Thurgadin, so I'm sure they are available there.  Not sure of other places.<br>
<br>
9) Put the the skin, the feather, the oil, the vial, and the pattern in your sewing kit.<br>
<br>
10) Pray<br>
<br>
11) Close your eyes<br>
<br>
12) Hit Combine<br>
<br>
13) Pray<br>
<br>
14) Open your eyes<br>
<br>
The result is a 6 slot quiver with weight reduction and like 20% bow haste. <br>
<br>
It's not trivial until a skill of like 220 in tailoring.<br>
<br>
Good luck.<br>
<br>
By the way, I have all the components, and I'm just looking for someone with a really high skill to hit combine for me.  Drop a reply if you know a Grandmaster Tailor for hire.<br>
